Module com.example.bankgui

Package com.example.bankgui

package com.example.bankgui
  • Classes
    Class
    Description
    Account
    The Account class is an abstract class that is the general type of the other account types; each account has a profile that uniquely identifies the account holder.
    AccountDatabase
    The AccountDatabase stores a list of all of the opened accounts, with methods to modify the list and the accounts in it
    Checking
    The Checking class extends the Account class without defining any additional instance variable, but defines the constants for interest rate and fee.
    CollegeChecking
    The CollegeChecking class extends the Checking class; includes one instance variable only, and defines the constants for interest rate and fee.
    Date
    The Date class represents a date with a year, month, and day
    JUnitAccountDatabase
    JUnit class for testing the close method in AccountDatabase
    JUnitDate
    JUnit class for testing the isValid method in Date
    MoneyMarket
    The MoneyMarket class extends the Savings class; includes one instance variable only, and defines the constants for interest rate and fee.
    Profile
    The Profile class is an account holder
    Savings
    The Savings class extends the Account class; includes one instance variable only, and defines the constants for interest rate and fee.
    TestProject2
    Main class for running JUnit tests
    TransactionManagerController
    The TransactionManagerController handles the events
    TransactionManagerMain
    The TransactionManagerMain launches the application
